Pharmacy Inventory Database (SQL)
For this project, I designed a pharmacy inventory database to practice creating tables, inserting realistic medication data, and running analytical queries. 
The goal was to simulate how a small pharmacy might track its stock levels, pricing, and product availability. This project helped me apply SQL concepts in a more practical, real-world way.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
/*
Pharmacy store project requirements:
- Create a table
- Include at least 5 columns
- Insert at least 15 items
- Order items by price
- Show at least one statistic
*/

-- Create the pharmacy inventory table
CREATE TABLE mendezPharmacy (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,     -- Unique ID for each item
    name TEXT,                  -- Medication name
    Quantity INTEGER,           -- Number of packages in stock
    Package_Size INTEGER,       -- Tablets/capsules per package
    Price_in_dollars INTEGER    -- Package price
);

-- Insert 15 medication entries
INSERT INTO mendezPharmacy VALUES (1, "Atorvastatin 5mg", 1, 30, 4 );
